                    "analysis": "The analyzed binary is a sophisticated backdoor or information stealer utilizing multiple layers of obfuscation and anti-analysis techniques. It employs a custom import resolver (sub_40182a, sub_401ac3) to dynamically load Windows APIs, bypassing static import table analysis. The sample features an internal stream cipher (sub_40171c, sub_4017aa) for decrypting embedded strings and payloads. Core malicious behaviors include: 1) Information gathering and screen capture, saving data as .BMP files (sub_404255); 2) Command and Control (C2) communication via HTTP POST requests using Base64-encoded buffers (sub_4031ee, sub_4012a4); 3) Establishing persistence through registry modifications (sub_404037); and 4) Extensive file system enumeration and potential exfiltration (sub_4067ad, sub_405490). Relevant IOCs include the SHA256 hash fb76b4a667c6d790c39fcc93a3aac8cd2a224f0eb9ece4ecfd7825f606c2a8b6 and the use of the Base64 alphabet in sub_4012a4.",
